48/*
49 * C macros to byte swap integral quantities.
50 */
51
52#define SWAP_BYTE(X) do { (void) &(X); } while (/*CONSTCOND*/0)
53#define SWAP_IDENT(X) do { (void) &(X); } while (/*CONSTCOND*/0)
54#define SWAP_HALF(X) do { \
55 uint16_t _x = (uint16_t) (X); \
56 uint32_t _t = _x & 0xFFU; \
57 _t <<= 8U; _x >>= 8U; _t |= _x & 0xFFU; \
58 (X) = (uint16_t) _t; \
59 } while (/*CONSTCOND*/0)
60#define _SWAP_WORD(X, T) do { \
61 uint32_t _x = (uint32_t) (X); \
62 uint32_t _t = _x & 0xFF; \
63 _t <<= 8; _x >>= 8; _t |= _x & 0xFF; \
64 _t <<= 8; _x >>= 8; _t |= _x & 0xFF; \
65 _t <<= 8; _x >>= 8; _t |= _x & 0xFF; \
66 (X) = (T) _t; \
67 } while (/*CONSTCOND*/0)
68#define SWAP_ADDR32(X) _SWAP_WORD(X, Elf32_Addr)
69#define SWAP_OFF32(X) _SWAP_WORD(X, Elf32_Off)
70#define SWAP_SWORD(X) _SWAP_WORD(X, Elf32_Sword)
71#define SWAP_WORD(X) _SWAP_WORD(X, Elf32_Word)
72#define _SWAP_WORD64(X, T) do { \
73 uint64_t _x = (uint64_t) (X); \
74 uint64_t _t = _x & 0xFF; \
75 _t <<= 8; _x >>= 8; _t |= _x & 0xFF; \
76 _t <<= 8; _x >>= 8; _t |= _x & 0xFF; \
77 _t <<= 8; _x >>= 8; _t |= _x & 0xFF; \
78 _t <<= 8; _x >>= 8; _t |= _x & 0xFF; \
79 _t <<= 8; _x >>= 8; _t |= _x & 0xFF; \
80 _t <<= 8; _x >>= 8; _t |= _x & 0xFF; \
81 _t <<= 8; _x >>= 8; _t |= _x & 0xFF; \
82 (X) = (T) _t; \
83 } while (/*CONSTCOND*/0)
84#define SWAP_ADDR64(X) _SWAP_WORD64(X, Elf64_Addr)
85#define SWAP_LWORD(X) _SWAP_WORD64(X, Elf64_Lword)
86#define SWAP_OFF64(X) _SWAP_WORD64(X, Elf64_Off)
87#define SWAP_SXWORD(X) _SWAP_WORD64(X, Elf64_Sxword)
88#define SWAP_XWORD(X) _SWAP_WORD64(X, Elf64_Xword)
89
90/*
91 * C macros to write out various integral values.
92 *
93 * Note:
94 * - The destination pointer could be unaligned.
95 * - Values are written out in native byte order.
96 * - The destination pointer is incremented after the write.
97 */
98#define WRITE_BYTE(P,X) do { \
99 unsigned char *const _p = (unsigned char *) (P); \
100 _p[0] = (unsigned char) (X); \
101 (P) = _p + 1; \
102 } while (/*CONSTCOND*/0)
103#define WRITE_HALF(P,X) do { \
104 union { \
105 uint16_t val; \
106 uint8_t bytes[2]; \
107 } _t; \
108 unsigned char *const _p = (void *) (P); \
109 _t.val = (X); \
110 _p[0] = _t.bytes[0]; \
111 _p[1] = _t.bytes[1]; \
112 (P) = (void *)(_p + 2); \
113 } while (/*CONSTCOND*/0)
114#define WRITE_WORD(P,X) do { \
115 union { \
116 uint32_t val; \
117 uint8_t bytes[4]; \
118 } _t; \
119 unsigned char *const _p = (void *) (P); \
120 _t.val = (X); \
121 _p[0] = _t.bytes[0]; \
122 _p[1] = _t.bytes[1]; \
123 _p[2] = _t.bytes[2]; \
124 _p[3] = _t.bytes[3]; \
125 (P) = (void *)(_p + 4); \
126 } while (/*CONSTCOND*/0)
127#define WRITE_ADDR32(P,X) WRITE_WORD(P,X)
128#define WRITE_OFF32(P,X) WRITE_WORD(P,X)
129#define WRITE_SWORD(P,X) WRITE_WORD(P,X)
130#define WRITE_WORD64(P,X) do { \
131 union { \
132 uint64_t val; \
133 uint8_t bytes[8]; \
134 } _t; \
135 unsigned char *const _p = (void *) (P); \
136 _t.val = (X); \
137 _p[0] = _t.bytes[0]; \
138 _p[1] = _t.bytes[1]; \
139 _p[2] = _t.bytes[2]; \
140 _p[3] = _t.bytes[3]; \
141 _p[4] = _t.bytes[4]; \
142 _p[5] = _t.bytes[5]; \
143 _p[6] = _t.bytes[6]; \
144 _p[7] = _t.bytes[7]; \
145 (P) = (void *)(_p + 8); \
146 } while (/*CONSTCOND*/0)
147#define WRITE_ADDR64(P,X) WRITE_WORD64(P,X)
148#define WRITE_LWORD(P,X) WRITE_WORD64(P,X)
149#define WRITE_OFF64(P,X) WRITE_WORD64(P,X)
150#define WRITE_SXWORD(P,X) WRITE_WORD64(P,X)
151#define WRITE_XWORD(P,X) WRITE_WORD64(P,X)
152#define WRITE_IDENT(P,X) do { \
153 (void) memcpy((P), (X), sizeof((X))); \
154 (P) = (P) + EI_NIDENT; \
155 } while (/*CONSTCOND*/0)
156
157/*
158 * C macros to read in various integral values.
159 *
160 * Note:
161 * - The source pointer could be unaligned.
162 * - Values are read in native byte order.
163 * - The source pointer is incremented appropriately.
164 */
165
166#define READ_BYTE(P,X) do { \
167 const unsigned char *const _p = \
168 (const void *) (P); \
169 (X) = _p[0]; \
170 (P) = (P) + 1; \
171 } while (/*CONSTCOND*/0)
172#define READ_HALF(P,X) do { \
173 uint16_t _t; \
174 unsigned char *const _q = (unsigned char *) &_t; \
175 const unsigned char *const _p = \
176 (const unsigned char *) (P); \
177 _q[0] = _p[0]; \
178 _q[1] = _p[1]; \
179 (P) = (P) + 2; \
180 (X) = _t; \
181 } while (/*CONSTCOND*/0)
182#define _READ_WORD(P,X,T) do { \
183 uint32_t _t; \
184 unsigned char *const _q = (unsigned char *) &_t; \
185 const unsigned char *const _p = \
186 (const unsigned char *) (P); \
187 _q[0] = _p[0]; \
188 _q[1] = _p[1]; \
189 _q[2] = _p[2]; \
190 _q[3] = _p[3]; \
191 (P) = (P) + 4; \
192 (X) = (T) _t; \
193 } while (/*CONSTCOND*/0)
194#define READ_ADDR32(P,X) _READ_WORD(P, X, Elf32_Addr)
195#define READ_OFF32(P,X) _READ_WORD(P, X, Elf32_Off)
196#define READ_SWORD(P,X) _READ_WORD(P, X, Elf32_Sword)
197#define READ_WORD(P,X) _READ_WORD(P, X, Elf32_Word)
198#define _READ_WORD64(P,X,T) do { \
199 uint64_t _t; \
200 unsigned char *const _q = (unsigned char *) &_t; \
201 const unsigned char *const _p = \
202 (const unsigned char *) (P); \
203 _q[0] = _p[0]; \
204 _q[1] = _p[1]; \
205 _q[2] = _p[2]; \
206 _q[3] = _p[3]; \
207 _q[4] = _p[4]; \
208 _q[5] = _p[5]; \
209 _q[6] = _p[6]; \
210 _q[7] = _p[7]; \
211 (P) = (P) + 8; \
212 (X) = (T) _t; \
213 } while (/*CONSTCOND*/0)
214#define READ_ADDR64(P,X) _READ_WORD64(P, X, Elf64_Addr)
215#define READ_LWORD(P,X) _READ_WORD64(P, X, Elf64_Lword)
216#define READ_OFF64(P,X) _READ_WORD64(P, X, Elf64_Off)
217#define READ_SXWORD(P,X) _READ_WORD64(P, X, Elf64_Sxword)
218#define READ_XWORD(P,X) _READ_WORD64(P, X, Elf64_Xword)
219#define READ_IDENT(P,X) do { \
220 (void) memcpy((X), (P), sizeof((X))); \
221 (P) = (P) + EI_NIDENT; \
222 } while (/*CONSTCOND*/0)
223
224#define ROUNDUP2(V,N) (V) = ((((V) + (N) - 1)) & ~((N) - 1))

228static int
229_libelf_cvt_ADDR32_tof(unsigned char *dst, size_t dsz, unsigned char *src,
230 size_t count, int byteswap)
231{
232 Elf32_Addr t, *s = (Elf32_Addr *) (uintptr_t) src;
233 size_t c;
234
235 (void) &dsz;
236
237 if (!byteswap) {
238 (void) memcpy(dst, src, count * sizeof(*s));
239 return (1);
240 }
241
242 for (c = 0; c < count; c++) {
243 t = *s++;
244 SWAP_ADDR32(t);
245 WRITE_ADDR32(dst,t);
246 }
247
248 return (1);
249}

260

322static int
323_libelf_cvt_CAP32_tof(unsigned char *dst, size_t dsz, unsigned char *src,
324 size_t count, int byteswap)
325{
326 Elf32_Cap t, *s;
327 size_t c;
328
329 (void) &dsz;
330
331 s = (Elf32_Cap *) (uintptr_t) src;
332 for (c = 0; c < count; c++) {
333 t = *s++;
334 if (byteswap) {
335 /* Swap an Elf32_Cap */
336 SWAP_WORD(t.c_tag);
337 SWAP_WORD(t.c_un.c_val);
338 /**/
339 }
340 /* Write an Elf32_Cap */
341 WRITE_WORD(dst,t.c_tag);
342 WRITE_WORD(dst,t.c_un.c_val);
343 /**/
344 }
345
346 return (1);
347}

349static int
350_libelf_cvt_CAP32_tom(unsigned char *dst, size_t dsz, unsigned char *src,
351 size_t count, int byteswap)
352{
353 Elf32_Cap t, *d;
354 unsigned char *s,*s0;
355 size_t fsz;
356
357 fsz = elf32_fsize(ELF_T_CAP, (size_t) 1, EV_CURRENT);
358 d = ((Elf32_Cap *) (uintptr_t) dst) + (count - 1);
359 s0 = src + (count - 1) * fsz;
360
361 if (dsz < count * sizeof(Elf32_Cap))
362 return (0);
363
364 while (count--) {
365 s = s0;
366 /* Read an Elf32_Cap */
367 READ_WORD(s,t.c_tag);
368 READ_WORD(s,t.c_un.c_val);
369 /**/
370 if (byteswap) {
371 /* Swap an Elf32_Cap */
372 SWAP_WORD(t.c_tag);
373 SWAP_WORD(t.c_un.c_val);
374 /**/
375 }
376 *d-- = t; s0 -= fsz;
377 }
378
379 return (1);
380}

562static int
563_libelf_cvt_EHDR32_tof(unsigned char *dst, size_t dsz, unsigned char *src,
564 size_t count, int byteswap)
565{
566 Elf32_Ehdr t, *s;
567 size_t c;
568
569 (void) &dsz;
570
571 s = (Elf32_Ehdr *) (uintptr_t) src;
572 for (c = 0; c < count; c++) {
573 t = *s++;
574 if (byteswap) {
575 /* Swap an Elf32_Ehdr */
576 SWAP_IDENT(t.e_ident);
577 SWAP_HALF(t.e_type);
578 SWAP_HALF(t.e_machine);
579 SWAP_WORD(t.e_version);
580 SWAP_ADDR32(t.e_entry);
581 SWAP_OFF32(t.e_phoff);
582 SWAP_OFF32(t.e_shoff);
583 SWAP_WORD(t.e_flags);
584 SWAP_HALF(t.e_ehsize);
585 SWAP_HALF(t.e_phentsize);
586 SWAP_HALF(t.e_phnum);
587 SWAP_HALF(t.e_shentsize);
588 SWAP_HALF(t.e_shnum);
589 SWAP_HALF(t.e_shstrndx);
590 /**/
591 }
592 /* Write an Elf32_Ehdr */
593 WRITE_IDENT(dst,t.e_ident);
594 WRITE_HALF(dst,t.e_type);
595 WRITE_HALF(dst,t.e_machine);
596 WRITE_WORD(dst,t.e_version);
597 WRITE_ADDR32(dst,t.e_entry);
598 WRITE_OFF32(dst,t.e_phoff);
599 WRITE_OFF32(dst,t.e_shoff);
600 WRITE_WORD(dst,t.e_flags);
601 WRITE_HALF(dst,t.e_ehsize);
602 WRITE_HALF(dst,t.e_phentsize);
603 WRITE_HALF(dst,t.e_phnum);
604 WRITE_HALF(dst,t.e_shentsize);
605 WRITE_HALF(dst,t.e_shnum);
606 WRITE_HALF(dst,t.e_shstrndx);
607 /**/
608 }
609
610 return (1);
611}

613static int
614_libelf_cvt_EHDR32_tom(unsigned char *dst, size_t dsz, unsigned char *src,
615 size_t count, int byteswap)
616{
617 Elf32_Ehdr t, *d;
618 unsigned char *s,*s0;
619 size_t fsz;
620
621 fsz = elf32_fsize(ELF_T_EHDR, (size_t) 1, EV_CURRENT);
622 d = ((Elf32_Ehdr *) (uintptr_t) dst) + (count - 1);
623 s0 = src + (count - 1) * fsz;
624
625 if (dsz < count * sizeof(Elf32_Ehdr))
626 return (0);
627
628 while (count--) {
629 s = s0;
630 /* Read an Elf32_Ehdr */
631 READ_IDENT(s,t.e_ident);
632 READ_HALF(s,t.e_type);
633 READ_HALF(s,t.e_machine);
634 READ_WORD(s,t.e_version);
635 READ_ADDR32(s,t.e_entry);
636 READ_OFF32(s,t.e_phoff);
637 READ_OFF32(s,t.e_shoff);
638 READ_WORD(s,t.e_flags);
639 READ_HALF(s,t.e_ehsize);
640 READ_HALF(s,t.e_phentsize);
641 READ_HALF(s,t.e_phnum);

2002 size_t count, int byteswap)
2003{
2004 Elf64_Sym t, *s;
2005 size_t c;
2006
2007 (void) &dsz;
2008
2009 s = (Elf64_Sym *) (uintptr_t) src;
2010 for (c = 0; c < count; c++) {
2011 t = *s++;
2012 if (byteswap) {
2013 /* Swap an Elf64_Sym */
2014 SWAP_WORD(t.st_name);
2015 SWAP_BYTE(t.st_info);
2016 SWAP_BYTE(t.st_other);
2017 SWAP_HALF(t.st_shndx);
2018 SWAP_ADDR64(t.st_value);
2019 SWAP_XWORD(t.st_size);
2020 /**/
2021 }
2022 /* Write an Elf64_Sym */
2023 WRITE_WORD(dst,t.st_name);
2024 WRITE_BYTE(dst,t.st_info);
2025 WRITE_BYTE(dst,t.st_other);
2026 WRITE_HALF(dst,t.st_shndx);
2027 WRITE_ADDR64(dst,t.st_value);
2028 WRITE_XWORD(dst,t.st_size);
2029 /**/
2030 }
2031
2032 return (1);
2033}

2035static int
2036_libelf_cvt_SYM64_tom(unsigned char *dst, size_t dsz, unsigned char *src,
2037 size_t count, int byteswap)
2038{
2039 Elf64_Sym t, *d;
2040 unsigned char *s,*s0;
2041 size_t fsz;
2042
2043 fsz = elf64_fsize(ELF_T_SYM, (size_t) 1, EV_CURRENT);
2044 d = ((Elf64_Sym *) (uintptr_t) dst) + (count - 1);
2045 s0 = src + (count - 1) * fsz;
2046
2047 if (dsz < count * sizeof(Elf64_Sym))
2048 return (0);
2049
2050 while (count--) {
2051 s = s0;
2052 /* Read an Elf64_Sym */
2053 READ_WORD(s,t.st_name);
2054 READ_BYTE(s,t.st_info);
2055 READ_BYTE(s,t.st_other);
2056 READ_HALF(s,t.st_shndx);
2057 READ_ADDR64(s,t.st_value);
2058 READ_XWORD(s,t.st_size);
2059 /**/
2060 if (byteswap) {
2061 /* Swap an Elf64_Sym */
2062 SWAP_WORD(t.st_name);
2063 SWAP_BYTE(t.st_info);
2064 SWAP_BYTE(t.st_other);
2065 SWAP_HALF(t.st_shndx);
2066 SWAP_ADDR64(t.st_value);
2067 SWAP_XWORD(t.st_size);
2068 /**/
2069 }
2070 *d-- = t; s0 -= fsz;
2071 }
2072
2073 return (1);
2074}

2079{

2082

2086 (void) memcpy(dst, src, count * sizeof(*s));

2091 t = *s++;
2092 SWAP_WORD(t);
2093 WRITE_WORD(dst,t);

2095
2096 return (1);

2171static int
2172_libelf_cvt_VDEF32_tof(unsigned char *dst, size_t dsz, unsigned char *src,
2173 size_t count, int byteswap)
2174{
2175 Elf32_Verdef t;
2176 Elf32_Verdaux a;
2177 const size_t verfsz = 20;
2178 const size_t auxfsz = 8;
2179 const size_t vermsz = sizeof(Elf32_Verdef);
2180 const size_t auxmsz = sizeof(Elf32_Verdaux);
2181 unsigned char * const dstend = dst + dsz;
2182 unsigned char * const srcend = src + count;
2183 unsigned char *dtmp, *dstaux, *srcaux;
2184 Elf32_Word aux, anext, cnt, vnext;
2185
2186 for (dtmp = dst, vnext = ~0U;
2187 vnext != 0 && dtmp + verfsz <= dstend && src + vermsz <= srcend;
2188 dtmp += vnext, src += vnext) {
2189
2190 /* Read in an Elf32_Verdef structure. */
2191 t = *((Elf32_Verdef *) (uintptr_t) src);
2192
2193 aux = t.vd_aux;
2194 cnt = t.vd_cnt;
2195 vnext = t.vd_next;
2196
2197 if (byteswap) {
2198 /* Swap an Elf32_Verdef */
2199 SWAP_HALF(t.vd_version);
2200 SWAP_HALF(t.vd_flags);
2201 SWAP_HALF(t.vd_ndx);
2202 SWAP_HALF(t.vd_cnt);
2203 SWAP_WORD(t.vd_hash);
2204 SWAP_WORD(t.vd_aux);
2205 SWAP_WORD(t.vd_next);
2206 /**/
2207 }
2208
2209 dst = dtmp;
2210 /* Write an Elf32_Verdef */
2211 WRITE_HALF(dst,t.vd_version);
2212 WRITE_HALF(dst,t.vd_flags);
2213 WRITE_HALF(dst,t.vd_ndx);
2214 WRITE_HALF(dst,t.vd_cnt);
2215 WRITE_WORD(dst,t.vd_hash);
2216 WRITE_WORD(dst,t.vd_aux);
2217 WRITE_WORD(dst,t.vd_next);
2218 /**/
2219
2220 if (aux < verfsz)
2221 return (0);
2222
2223 /* Process AUX entries. */
2224 for (anext = ~0U, dstaux = dtmp + aux, srcaux = src + aux;
2225 cnt != 0 && anext != 0 && dstaux + auxfsz <= dstend &&
2226 srcaux + auxmsz <= srcend;
2227 dstaux += anext, srcaux += anext, cnt--) {
2228
2229 /* Read in an Elf32_Verdaux structure. */
2230 a = *((Elf32_Verdaux *) (uintptr_t) srcaux);
2231 anext = a.vda_next;
2232
2233 if (byteswap) {
2234 /* Swap an Elf32_Verdaux */
2235 SWAP_WORD(a.vda_name);
2236 SWAP_WORD(a.vda_next);
2237 /**/
2238 }
2239
2240 dst = dstaux;
2241 /* Write an Elf32_Verdaux */
2242 WRITE_WORD(dst,a.vda_name);
2243 WRITE_WORD(dst,a.vda_next);
2244 /**/
2245 }
2246
2247 if (anext || cnt)
2248 return (0);
2249 }
2250
2251 if (vnext)
2252 return (0);
2253
2254 return (1);
2255}

2662 READ_HALF(s,a.vna_flags);
2663 READ_HALF(s,a.vna_other);
2664 READ_WORD(s,a.vna_name);
2665 READ_WORD(s,a.vna_next);
2666 /**/
2667
2668 if (byteswap) {
2669 /* Swap an Elf32_Vernaux */
2670 SWAP_WORD(a.vna_hash);
2671 SWAP_HALF(a.vna_flags);
2672 SWAP_HALF(a.vna_other);
2673 SWAP_WORD(a.vna_name);
2674 SWAP_WORD(a.vna_next);
2675 /**/
2676 }
2677
2678 anext = a.vna_next;
2679
2680 ap = ((Elf32_Vernaux *) (uintptr_t) dstaux);
2681 *ap = a;
2682 }
2683
2684 if (anext || cnt)
2685 return (0);
2686 }
2687
2688 if (vnext)
2689 return (0);
2690
2691 return (1);
2692}
2693
2694static int
2695_libelf_cvt_VNEED64_tof(unsigned char *dst, size_t dsz, unsigned char *src,
2696 size_t count, int byteswap)
2697{
2698 Elf64_Verneed t;
2699 Elf64_Vernaux a;
2700 const size_t verfsz = 16;
2701 const size_t auxfsz = 16;
2702 const size_t vermsz = sizeof(Elf64_Verneed);
2703 const size_t auxmsz = sizeof(Elf64_Vernaux);
2704 unsigned char * const dstend = dst + dsz;
2705 unsigned char * const srcend = src + count;
2706 unsigned char *dtmp, *dstaux, *srcaux;
2707 Elf64_Word aux, anext, cnt, vnext;
2708
2709 for (dtmp = dst, vnext = ~0U;
2710 vnext != 0 && dtmp + verfsz <= dstend && src + vermsz <= srcend;
2711 dtmp += vnext, src += vnext) {
2712
2713 /* Read in an Elf64_Verneed structure. */
2714 t = *((Elf64_Verneed *) (uintptr_t) src);
2715
2716 aux = t.vn_aux;
2717 cnt = t.vn_cnt;
2718 vnext = t.vn_next;
2719
2720 if (byteswap) {
2721 /* Swap an Elf64_Verneed */
2722 SWAP_HALF(t.vn_version);
2723 SWAP_HALF(t.vn_cnt);
2724 SWAP_WORD(t.vn_file);
2725 SWAP_WORD(t.vn_aux);
2726 SWAP_WORD(t.vn_next);
2727 /**/
2728 }
2729
2730 dst = dtmp;
2731 /* Write an Elf64_Verneed */
2732 WRITE_HALF(dst,t.vn_version);
2733 WRITE_HALF(dst,t.vn_cnt);
2734 WRITE_WORD(dst,t.vn_file);
2735 WRITE_WORD(dst,t.vn_aux);
2736 WRITE_WORD(dst,t.vn_next);
2737 /**/
2738
2739 if (aux < verfsz)
2740 return (0);
2741
2742 /* Process AUX entries. */
2743 for (anext = ~0U, dstaux = dtmp + aux, srcaux = src + aux;
2744 cnt != 0 && anext != 0 && dstaux + auxfsz <= dstend &&
2745 srcaux + auxmsz <= srcend;
2746 dstaux += anext, srcaux += anext, cnt--) {
2747
2748 /* Read in an Elf64_Vernaux structure. */
2749 a = *((Elf64_Vernaux *) (uintptr_t) srcaux);
2750 anext = a.vna_next;
2751
2752 if (byteswap) {
2753 /* Swap an Elf64_Vernaux */
2754 SWAP_WORD(a.vna_hash);
2755 SWAP_HALF(a.vna_flags);
2756 SWAP_HALF(a.vna_other);
2757 SWAP_WORD(a.vna_name);
2758 SWAP_WORD(a.vna_next);
2759 /**/
2760 }
2761
2762 dst = dstaux;
2763 /* Write an Elf64_Vernaux */
2764 WRITE_WORD(dst,a.vna_hash);
2765 WRITE_HALF(dst,a.vna_flags);
2766 WRITE_HALF(dst,a.vna_other);
2767 WRITE_WORD(dst,a.vna_name);
2768 WRITE_WORD(dst,a.vna_next);
2769 /**/
2770 }
2771
2772 if (anext || cnt)
2773 return (0);
2774 }
2775
2776 if (vnext)
2777 return (0);
2778
2779 return (1);
2780}

2782static int
2783_libelf_cvt_VNEED64_tom(unsigned char *dst, size_t dsz, unsigned char *src,
2784 size_t count, int byteswap)
2785{
2786 Elf64_Verneed t, *dp;
2787 Elf64_Vernaux a, *ap;
2788 const size_t verfsz = 16;
2789 const size_t auxfsz = 16;
2790 const size_t vermsz = sizeof(Elf64_Verneed);
2791 const size_t auxmsz = sizeof(Elf64_Vernaux);
2792 unsigned char * const dstend = dst + dsz;
2793 unsigned char * const srcend = src + count;
2794 unsigned char *dstaux, *s, *srcaux, *stmp;
2795 Elf64_Word aux, anext, cnt, vnext;
2796
2797 for (stmp = src, vnext = ~0U;
2798 vnext != 0 && stmp + verfsz <= srcend && dst + vermsz <= dstend;
2799 stmp += vnext, dst += vnext) {
2800
2801 /* Read in a VNEED structure. */
2802 s = stmp;
2803 /* Read an Elf64_Verneed */
2804 READ_HALF(s,t.vn_version);
2805 READ_HALF(s,t.vn_cnt);
2806 READ_WORD(s,t.vn_file);
2807 READ_WORD(s,t.vn_aux);
2808 READ_WORD(s,t.vn_next);
2809 /**/
2810 if (byteswap) {
2811 /* Swap an Elf64_Verneed */
2812 SWAP_HALF(t.vn_version);
2813 SWAP_HALF(t.vn_cnt);
2814 SWAP_WORD(t.vn_file);
2815 SWAP_WORD(t.vn_aux);
2816 SWAP_WORD(t.vn_next);
2817 /**/
2818 }
2819
2820 dp = (Elf64_Verneed *) (uintptr_t) dst;
2821 *dp = t;
2822
2823 aux = t.vn_aux;
2824 cnt = t.vn_cnt;
2825 vnext = t.vn_next;
2826
2827 if (aux < vermsz)
2828 return (0);
2829
2830 /* Process AUX entries. */
2831 for (anext = ~0U, dstaux = dst + aux, srcaux = stmp + aux;
2832 cnt != 0 && anext != 0 && dstaux + auxmsz <= dstend &&
2833 srcaux + auxfsz <= srcend;
2834 dstaux += anext, srcaux += anext, cnt--) {
2835
2836 s = srcaux;
2837 /* Read an Elf64_Vernaux */
2838 READ_WORD(s,a.vna_hash);
2839 READ_HALF(s,a.vna_flags);
2840 READ_HALF(s,a.vna_other);
2841 READ_WORD(s,a.vna_name);
2842 READ_WORD(s,a.vna_next);
2843 /**/
2844
2845 if (byteswap) {
2846 /* Swap an Elf64_Vernaux */
2847 SWAP_WORD(a.vna_hash);
2848 SWAP_HALF(a.vna_flags);
2849 SWAP_HALF(a.vna_other);
2850 SWAP_WORD(a.vna_name);
2851 SWAP_WORD(a.vna_next);
2852 /**/
2853 }
2854
2855 anext = a.vna_next;
2856
2857 ap = ((Elf64_Vernaux *) (uintptr_t) dstaux);
2858 *ap = a;
2859 }
2860
2861 if (anext || cnt)
2862 return (0);
2863 }
2864
2865 if (vnext)
2866 return (0);
2867
2868 return (1);
2869}

2872/*
2873 * Sections of type ELF_T_BYTE are never byteswapped, consequently a
2874 * simple memcpy suffices for both directions of conversion.
2875 */
2876
2877/*ARGSUSED*/
2878static int
2879_libelf_cvt_BYTE_tox(unsigned char *dst, size_t dsz, unsigned char *src,
2880 size_t count, int byteswap)
2881{
2882 (void) &byteswap;
2883 if (dsz < count)
2884 return (0);
2885 if (dst != src)
2886 (void) memcpy(dst, src, count);
2887 return (1);
2888}

2890/*
2891 * Sections of type ELF_T_GNUHASH start with a header containing 4 32-bit
2892 * words. Bloom filter data comes next, followed by hash buckets and the
2893 * hash chain.
2894 *
2895 * Bloom filter words are 64 bit wide on ELFCLASS64 objects and are 32 bit
2896 * wide on ELFCLASS32 objects. The other objects in this section are 32
2897 * bits wide.
2898 *
2899 * Argument srcsz denotes the number of bytes to be converted. In the
2900 * 32-bit case we need to translate srcsz to a count of 32-bit words.
2901 */
2902
2903static int
2904_libelf_cvt_GNUHASH32_tom(unsigned char *dst, size_t dsz, unsigned char *src,
2905 size_t srcsz, int byteswap)
2906{
2907 return (_libelf_cvt_WORD_tom(dst, dsz, src, srcsz / sizeof(uint32_t),
2908 byteswap));
2909}
2910
2911static int
2912_libelf_cvt_GNUHASH32_tof(unsigned char *dst, size_t dsz, unsigned char *src,
2913 size_t srcsz, int byteswap)
2914{
2915 return (_libelf_cvt_WORD_tof(dst, dsz, src, srcsz / sizeof(uint32_t),
2916 byteswap));
2917}
2918
2919static int
2920_libelf_cvt_GNUHASH64_tom(unsigned char *dst, size_t dsz, unsigned char *src,
2921 size_t srcsz, int byteswap)
2922{
2923 size_t sz;
2924 uint64_t t64, *bloom64;
2925 Elf_GNU_Hash_Header *gh;
2926 uint32_t n, nbuckets, nchains, maskwords, shift2, symndx, t32;
2927 uint32_t *buckets, *chains;
2928
2929 sz = 4 * sizeof(uint32_t); /* File header is 4 words long. */
2930 if (dsz < sizeof(Elf_GNU_Hash_Header) || srcsz < sz)
2931 return (0);
2932
2933 /* Read in the section header and byteswap if needed. */
2934 READ_WORD(src, nbuckets);
2935 READ_WORD(src, symndx);
2936 READ_WORD(src, maskwords);
2937 READ_WORD(src, shift2);
2938
2939 srcsz -= sz;
2940
2941 if (byteswap) {
2942 SWAP_WORD(nbuckets);
2943 SWAP_WORD(symndx);
2944 SWAP_WORD(maskwords);
2945 SWAP_WORD(shift2);
2946 }
2947
2948 /* Check source buffer and destination buffer sizes. */
2949 sz = nbuckets * sizeof(uint32_t) + maskwords * sizeof(uint64_t);
2950 if (srcsz < sz || dsz < sz + sizeof(Elf_GNU_Hash_Header))
2951 return (0);
2952
2953 gh = (Elf_GNU_Hash_Header *) (uintptr_t) dst;
2954 gh->gh_nbuckets = nbuckets;
2955 gh->gh_symndx = symndx;
2956 gh->gh_maskwords = maskwords;
2957 gh->gh_shift2 = shift2;
2958
2959 dsz -= sizeof(Elf_GNU_Hash_Header);
2960 dst += sizeof(Elf_GNU_Hash_Header);
2961
2962 bloom64 = (uint64_t *) (uintptr_t) dst;
2963
2964 /* Copy bloom filter data. */
2965 for (n = 0; n < maskwords; n++) {
2966 READ_XWORD(src, t64);
2967 if (byteswap)
2968 SWAP_XWORD(t64);
2969 bloom64[n] = t64;
2970 }
2971
2972 /* The hash buckets follows the bloom filter. */
2973 dst += maskwords * sizeof(uint64_t);
2974 buckets = (uint32_t *) (uintptr_t) dst;
2975
2976 for (n = 0; n < nbuckets; n++) {
2977 READ_WORD(src, t32);
2978 if (byteswap)
2979 SWAP_WORD(t32);
2980 buckets[n] = t32;
2981 }
2982
2983 dst += nbuckets * sizeof(uint32_t);
2984
2985 /* The hash chain follows the hash buckets. */
2986 dsz -= sz;
2987 srcsz -= sz;
2988
2989 if (dsz < srcsz) /* Destination lacks space. */
2990 return (0);
2991
2992 nchains = srcsz / sizeof(uint32_t);
2993 chains = (uint32_t *) (uintptr_t) dst;
2994
2995 for (n = 0; n < nchains; n++) {
2996 READ_WORD(src, t32);
2997 if (byteswap)
2998 SWAP_WORD(t32);
2999 *chains++ = t32;
3000 }
3001
3002 return (1);
3003}
3004
3005static int
3006_libelf_cvt_GNUHASH64_tof(unsigned char *dst, size_t dsz, unsigned char *src,
3007 size_t srcsz, int byteswap)
3008{
3009 uint32_t *s32;
3010 size_t sz, hdrsz;
3011 uint64_t *s64, t64;
3012 Elf_GNU_Hash_Header *gh;
3013 uint32_t maskwords, n, nbuckets, nchains, t0, t1, t2, t3, t32;
3014
3015 hdrsz = 4 * sizeof(uint32_t); /* Header is 4x32 bits. */
3016 if (dsz < hdrsz || srcsz < sizeof(Elf_GNU_Hash_Header))
3017 return (0);
3018
3019 gh = (Elf_GNU_Hash_Header *) (uintptr_t) src;
3020
3021 t0 = nbuckets = gh->gh_nbuckets;
3022 t1 = gh->gh_symndx;
3023 t2 = maskwords = gh->gh_maskwords;
3024 t3 = gh->gh_shift2;
3025
3026 src += sizeof(Elf_GNU_Hash_Header);
3027 srcsz -= sizeof(Elf_GNU_Hash_Header);
3028 dsz -= hdrsz;
3029
3030 sz = gh->gh_nbuckets * sizeof(uint32_t) + gh->gh_maskwords *
3031 sizeof(uint64_t);
3032
3033 if (srcsz < sz || dsz < sz)
3034 return (0);
3035
3036 /* Write out the header. */
3037 if (byteswap) {
3038 SWAP_WORD(t0);
3039 SWAP_WORD(t1);
3040 SWAP_WORD(t2);
3041 SWAP_WORD(t3);
3042 }
3043
3044 WRITE_WORD(dst, t0);
3045 WRITE_WORD(dst, t1);
3046 WRITE_WORD(dst, t2);
3047 WRITE_WORD(dst, t3);
3048
3049 /* Copy the bloom filter and the hash table. */
3050 s64 = (uint64_t *) (uintptr_t) src;
3051 for (n = 0; n < maskwords; n++) {
3052 t64 = *s64++;
3053 if (byteswap)
3054 SWAP_XWORD(t64);
3055 WRITE_WORD64(dst, t64);
3056 }
3057
3058 s32 = (uint32_t *) s64;
3059 for (n = 0; n < nbuckets; n++) {
3060 t32 = *s32++;
3061 if (byteswap)
3062 SWAP_WORD(t32);
3063 WRITE_WORD(dst, t32);
3064 }
3065
3066 srcsz -= sz;
3067 dsz -= sz;
3068
3069 /* Copy out the hash chains. */
3070 if (dsz < srcsz)
3071 return (0);
3072
3073 nchains = srcsz / sizeof(uint32_t);
3074 for (n = 0; n < nchains; n++) {
3075 t32 = *s32++;
3076 if (byteswap)
3077 SWAP_WORD(t32);
3078 WRITE_WORD(dst, t32);
3079 }
3080
3081 return (1);
3082}
3083
3084/*
3085 * Elf note structures comprise a fixed size header followed by variable
3086 * length strings. The fixed size header needs to be byte swapped, but
3087 * not the strings.
3088 *
3089 * Argument count denotes the total number of bytes to be converted.
3090 * The destination buffer needs to be at least count bytes in size.
3091 */
3092static int
3093_libelf_cvt_NOTE_tom(unsigned char *dst, size_t dsz, unsigned char *src,
3094 size_t count, int byteswap)
3095{
3096 uint32_t namesz, descsz, type;
3097 Elf_Note *en;
3098 size_t sz, hdrsz;
3099
3100 if (dsz < count) /* Destination buffer is too small. */
3101 return (0);
3102
3103 hdrsz = 3 * sizeof(uint32_t);
3104 if (count < hdrsz) /* Source too small. */
3105 return (0);
3106
3107 if (!byteswap) {
3108 (void) memcpy(dst, src, count);
3109 return (1);
3110 }
3111
3112 /* Process all notes in the section. */
3113 while (count > hdrsz) {
3114 /* Read the note header. */
3115 READ_WORD(src, namesz);
3116 READ_WORD(src, descsz);
3117 READ_WORD(src, type);
3118
3119 /* Translate. */
3120 SWAP_WORD(namesz);
3121 SWAP_WORD(descsz);
3122 SWAP_WORD(type);
3123
3124 /* Copy out the translated note header. */
3125 en = (Elf_Note *) (uintptr_t) dst;
3126 en->n_namesz = namesz;
3127 en->n_descsz = descsz;
3128 en->n_type = type;
3129
3130 dsz -= sizeof(Elf_Note);
3131 dst += sizeof(Elf_Note);
3132 count -= hdrsz;
3133
3134 ROUNDUP2(namesz, 4U);
3135 ROUNDUP2(descsz, 4U);
3136
3137 sz = namesz + descsz;
3138
3139 if (count < sz || dsz < sz) /* Buffers are too small. */
3140 return (0);
3141
3142 (void) memcpy(dst, src, sz);
3143
3144 src += sz;
3145 dst += sz;
3146
3147 count -= sz;
3148 dsz -= sz;
3149 }
3150
3151 return (1);
3152}
3153
3154static int
3155_libelf_cvt_NOTE_tof(unsigned char *dst, size_t dsz, unsigned char *src,
3156 size_t count, int byteswap)
3157{
3158 uint32_t namesz, descsz, type;
3159 Elf_Note *en;
3160 size_t sz;
3161
3162 if (dsz < count)
3163 return (0);
3164
3165 if (!byteswap) {
3166 (void) memcpy(dst, src, count);
3167 return (1);
3168 }
3169
3170 while (count > sizeof(Elf_Note)) {
3171
3172 en = (Elf_Note *) (uintptr_t) src;
3173 namesz = en->n_namesz;
3174 descsz = en->n_descsz;
3175 type = en->n_type;
3176
3177 sz = namesz;
3178 ROUNDUP2(sz, 4U);
3179 sz += descsz;
3180 ROUNDUP2(sz, 4U);
3181
3182 SWAP_WORD(namesz);
3183 SWAP_WORD(descsz);
3184 SWAP_WORD(type);
3185
3186 WRITE_WORD(dst, namesz);
3187 WRITE_WORD(dst, descsz);
3188 WRITE_WORD(dst, type);
3189
3190 src += sizeof(Elf_Note);
3191
3192 if (count < sz)
3193 sz = count;
3194
3195 (void) memcpy(dst, src, sz);
3196
3197 src += sz;
3198 dst += sz;
3199 count -= sz;
3200 }
3201
3202 return (1);
3203}

3387
3388int (*_libelf_get_translator(Elf_Type t, int direction, int elfclass))
3389 (unsigned char *_dst, size_t dsz, unsigned char *_src, size_t _cnt,
3390 int _byteswap)
3391{
3392 assert(elfclass == ELFCLASS32 || elfclass == ELFCLASS64);
3393 assert(direction == ELF_TOFILE || direction == ELF_TOMEMORY);
3394
3395 if (t >= ELF_T_NUM ||
3396 (elfclass != ELFCLASS32 && elfclass != ELFCLASS64) ||
3397 (direction != ELF_TOFILE && direction != ELF_TOMEMORY))
3398 return (NULL);
3399
3400 return ((elfclass == ELFCLASS32) ?
3401 (direction == ELF_TOFILE ? cvt[t].tof32 : cvt[t].tom32) :
3402 (direction == ELF_TOFILE ? cvt[t].tof64 : cvt[t].tom64));
3403}
